Ingredients (for one pizza)
---------------------------
220 grams of white flour (T45, or 00 if you can find italian flour. W170 or W200 - i.e. more gluten in best. Caputo 00 is good)
135 grams of water
2.3 grams of fresh yeast (1/4 of the quantity they tell you to use on the packaging, I use L'Hirondelle)
1.3 grams of salt (just taste)

mix everything, knead for 15-25 minutes until it start to feel like an old chewing-gum

let rest for 2-3 hour at room temperature or one night in fridge. Becarefull, il will try to escape from frige. 
